<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf656abe5-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2112"><num value="2112">§ 2112.</num><heading> Authority to change working hours</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In a port at which the customary working hours begin before 8 a.m. or end after 5 p.m., the Secretary may regulate the working hours of the officers and employees referred to in <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s2111">section 2111 of this title</ref> so that those hours conform to the prevailing working hours of the port. However—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf656abe6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2112/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the total period for which overtime pay may be required under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s2111">section 2111 of this title</ref> may not be more than 15 hours between any 2 periods of ordinary working hours on other than Sundays and holidays;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf656abe7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2112/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the length of the working day for the officers and employees involved may not be changed; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf656abe8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2112/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> the rate of overtime pay may not be changed.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf656abe9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/508">97 Stat. 508</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
